  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">OTP Bank Hungary (f. P Nemo, Bail-in Sub Debt)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The EBRD invested EUR 60 million in a subordinated bond issued by OTP Bank, as  part of a benchmark issuance of EUR 500 million. This is the first  MREL-eligible instrument issued by OTP Bank since BRRD introduction and new  MREL guidelines, and the bank&apos;s return to the Euromarket since pre-crisis  times. The Tier 2 capital eligible bonds have a 10-year maturity, are callable  after five years and are listed on the Luxembourg Stock Exchange.  The EBRD further invested EUR 75 million in a EUR 400 million green senior  preferred bond issuance by OTP Bank in July 2022. The MREL-eligible bond has a  3-year maturity, with a call option after the second year, and are listed on  the Luxembourg Stock Exchange.</narrative>
  </description>
